Calculation and visualization of $\Delta$ d/d and $\Delta \Psi$¶

  • 4-inch data
  • Calculate Δd/d $\psi$=0, $\psi$=120, $\psi$=-120
  • Take the difference from the neighboring pixel

Calculation results

  • |Δd/d| = 0.59 × 10-4
  • |∆ψ| < ∆p/L = 1.0 × 10−4rad (=0.0057◦)
  • The measurement data is below the measurement limit.

limitation principle¶

|Δd/d| < (Δpsin(2θB)/(2Ltan(θB))

  • L = 0.5 m
  • ∆λ/λ = 2.8 × 10−4
  • ∆p = 50 µm
  • Another limitation about the local lattice-plane curvature |∆ψ| arises from the geometrical consideration on a plane perpendicular to the diffraction plane.
  • |∆ψ| < ∆p/L.
  • |∆ψ| is smallerthan 1.0×10−4rad (=0.0057◦) for L=0.5 m.

experimental conditions for 4 inch data¶

  • Δp = 0.05 mm
  • L = 500 mm
  • GaN (112¯4) d = 1.004 Å
  • λ = 1.284 Å
  • incident angle: 0.58°
  • Bragg angle(θB) : 39.75°
  • 2θB: 79.5°
